# Quotes about models
# Tukey; 
#   "Statisticians, like artists, have a tendency to fall in love with their models.' --Tukey

# Dr. Keith Vorkink BYU devo March 28, 2017
#   We have a model that works, but we don't fully understand why

# Hocking:
#   If the goal is prediction we will do better with the "wrong model"
#   Poorly estimated model: (influenced observations, sparse data, collinearity)
#   Has biases in future prediction

# Subset Regression/Variable Selection
# Note: many people misunderstand this... thinking the data will somehow find the important effects
#   But it's really just "find a simple model that predicts well."

#   Tradeoff between prediction performance and parsimony (simple model that's easy to explain)